refactor(api): dashboard-driven image promotion (drops the workflow)

Pivots the Phase 7.1 promotion path from a GitHub Actions workflow
(triggered on merge) to a dashboard server endpoint (triggered by
the admin clicking Approve in the queue UI).

Rationale (now in ADR-015 "Promotion path - revised"):
- Single admin (7IBO) means the GitHub PR review UI isn't where
  merges happen anyway - the dashboard queue is.
- Doing the copy + URL rewrite + merge in one server-side
  transaction removes a class of race (merge-but-promote-hasn't-
  run-yet).
- Keeps the bytes off the public CDN until an explicit human OK.
- Centralises future validation/transformation (resize, optimize,
  NSFW later) in one server module instead of split between
  dashboard + workflow.

Removed:
- .github/workflows/promote-images.yml
- scripts/promote-staged-images.ts
  (the logic lives in apps/dashboard/api/admin-promote.ts now)

Added:
- packages/github-client/src/app-client.ts re-exports the Octokit
  type so consumers can annotate without depending on @octokit/rest
- packages/github-client/src/repo-ops.ts:
  - getPullRequest(prNumber) for the file list + head branch
  - mergePullRequest(prNumber, opts) for squash-merge
  - closePullRequest(prNumber) for the reject path
- apps/dashboard/api/admin-promote.ts:
  - promoteAndMergePR runs the full sequence: read changed image
    files from the PR head, collect staging:// keys, S3-copy
    pending/ to images/, push rewrite commits on the PR branch,
    squash-merge, best-effort delete pending/ sources.
  - rejectAndCleanupPR closes the PR + deletes the staged sources.
- apps/dashboard/api/server.ts:
  - POST /api/admin/promote { prNumber } (admin-only)
  - POST /api/admin/reject { prNumber } (admin-only)

The build guard in packages/schema-engine/src/cli/validate.ts
remains - catches any out-of-band merge that leaves a staging://
URL on main.

Until the Phase 7.3 queue UI ships, the admin can drive
promotion/rejection by hitting the endpoints directly; the wiring
is otherwise identical to what the UI will use.
